      "content": "This perspective reflects a growing urgency among climate scientists, who argue that the speed of warming demands immediate, large-scale deployment of all available low-carbon technologies. While some dismiss this as alarmism, the scientific consensus confirms that rapid decarbonization is necessary to meet international climate goals. Therefore, for those prioritizing emergency climate action, the need to swiftly scale up nuclear power is a rational, high-stakes calculation.",
      "source": "target",
